Chief justice David Maraga has warned contractors of the new courts in Mombasa against delays in completion. Justice Maraga said the Judiciary will not accept any delays of the courts which are expected to be complete by 2019. “You have started the construction well, please continue with the same speed. We do not want unnecessary delays,” he said. He asaid the delays will result in extra costs. He spoke in Mombasa yesterday after laying a foundation stone for the construction of modern courts named “Justice Towers”. He was accompanied by Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho and registrar of the Judiciary Anne Amadi, among other judicial and political officers. On Monday, the CJ opened the construction of the High Court in Kwale while on Tuesday, he commissioned works in Voi, Taita Taveta county.  